1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
250 g Lamb Mince
1 packet Couscous
1 packet Mint
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Fine Breadcrumbs
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 Lemon
1 sachet Chermoula Spice Blend
2 Radish
1 piece egg
1 drizzle olive oil
¾ cup boiling water (for the couscous)

• Boil the kettle.
• Thinly slice radish.
• Slice lemon into wedges.
• In a heatproof medium bowl, add couscous and chicken-style stock powder.
• Add the boiling water (3/4 cup for 2 people / 11/2 cups for 4 people) and stir to combine. Immediately cover with plate and leave for 5 minutes.
• Fluff up with a fork and set aside to cool slightly.

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl combine lamb mince, fine breadcrumbs, chermoula spice blend and the egg.
• Using damp hands, roll beef mixture into koftas about 8cm long and 2.5cm thick (3 per person).
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook koftas, turning regularly, until browned and cooked through, 10-12 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).

• To the bowl with the couscous, add radish, mixed salad leaves, a generous squeeze of lemon juice and drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide couscous salad between bowls.
• Top with chermoula lamb koftas.
• Drizzle over Greek-style yoghurt and tear over mint.
• Serve with remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!